The 20-year-old defender is wanted at Manchester United and the club have been in contact with his representatives over a potential move. Erik ten Hag wants to take the Dutchman to Old Trafford as part of his summer plans as he seeks to bring in some familiar faces ahead of his first season as Manchester United manager. Timber is keen on reuniting with Ten Hag and talks have already taken place between Manchester United and Ajax for the defender. -Advertisement- And it has been claimed that Ajax have already set their financial expectations for the sale of the young centre-back. The Dutch champions are prepared to sell the player for a fee of €35m in the summer transfer window. They are aware Ten Hag wants him and are open to letting the youngster go as long as their asking price is met. Manchester United are negotiating with Ajax and are confident of working out an agreement due to their prior good relationship with the club.